alternatives.transcript: missus culmer is a sixty two year old woman who presented to the emergency department today with shortness of breath and fatigue she was in her normal state of good health until about two weeks ago when she developed a cough chest pain rhinorrhea and fever which she described as a cold five days ago she noticed that while all of her other symptoms had resolved her chest pain fatigue and shortness of breath had actually gotten worse so three days ago she saw her family medicine doctor who recommended today that she come to the emergency department as the chest pain has continued to worsen she has hypertension for which she's been taking lisinopril ten milligrams for ten years and a cardiac catheter one year ago following an abnormal ekg showed no coronary artery disease her review of systems reveals fatigue eight pound weight gain in two weeks palpitations chest pain wheezing orthopnea dyspnea and lower leg myalgia and edema vitals show a temperature of ninety eight point six a heart rate of one ten a blood pressure of one thirty over ninety a respiratory rate of twenty and an spo two of ninety one percent on room air she was previously able to go to plus one lower extremity edema with equal dorsalis pedis pulses and nontender calves she had no cardiac bruise the lab showed troponin elevated at point one and bmp elevated at four thousand a chest my leading differential diagnosis is myocarditis with dilated cardiomyopathy in the new york health association class two heart association class two i think it's best if we admit her to telemetry and
